While researching cybercrime, I was most surprised by how simple phishing attacks can be and how easily people fall victim to them. Attackers often use basic psychological tricks such as urgency and fear rather than advanced technical methods. This made me realize that awareness is more important than technical knowledge in preventing such attacks. One habit I will personally change is verifying every link and message before taking action, especially those related to banking or personal accounts. I will also ensure that I never share OTPs or sensitive information under any circumstances. This task helped me understand that staying safe online requires constant attention and responsible digital behavior.
